The research aims to fill the knowledge gap on the frost formation phenomena occurring on the fin surface of the evaporator inside a domestic refrigerator. It consists of the following parts: 
- literature review of the topic, recognizing the current state and identifying a potential direction for further studies;
- numerical modeling of the process of evaporator clogging;
- mathematical calculations of the model using CFD tools, predicting the frost growth pace and profile;
- experimental validation of the model and conclusions.
The model can further be used for frost formation risk reduction on different 
solid surfaces which are in contact with high humidity. This may be implemented as a cost-reduction action for numerous projects in different fields 
of engineering.
